macro.title: Mortgage rates fall near 6% with GSEs set to boost MBS purchases
macro.what: Last week, the market responded to President Donald Trump’s directive for Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac to purchase $200 billion in mortgage-backed securities (MBS).
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.
